"Luo J.-J., Masson S., Behera S., Delecluse P., Gualdi S., Navarra A., Yamagata T.","South Pacific origin of the decadal ENSO-like variation as simulated by a coupled GCM",2003,"Geophysical Research Letters","30","24",,"CLM 1","1 - CLM 1-4",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-1642633368&partnerID=40&md5=4299f6d59a7f2ed310d912df974b5f88","Frontier Res. Syst. Global Change, 3173-25 Showa-machi, Yokohama, Kanagawa 236-0001, Japan; Lab. d'Ocanogr. Dynamique Climatol., Paris, France; Inst. of Natl. Geophys./Volcanology, v. Gobetti 101, Bologna 40129, Italy; Department of Earth/Planetary Sci., The University of Tokyo, Tokyo 113-0033, Japan","Luo, J.-J., Frontier Res. Syst. Global Change, 3173-25 Showa-machi, Yokohama, Kanagawa 236-0001, Japan; Masson, S., Frontier Res. Syst. Global Change, 3173-25 Showa-machi, Yokohama, Kanagawa 236-0001, Japan; Behera, S., Frontier Res. Syst. Global Change, 3173-25 Showa-machi, Yokohama, Kanagawa 236-0001, Japan; Delecluse, P., Lab. d'Ocanogr. Dynamique Climatol., Paris, France; Gualdi, S., Inst. of Natl. Geophys./Volcanology, v. Gobetti 101, Bologna 40129, Italy; Navarra, A., Inst. of Natl. Geophys./Volcanology, v. Gobetti 101, Bologna 40129, Italy; Yamagata, T., Department of Earth/Planetary Sci., The University of Tokyo, Tokyo 113-0033, Japan","The hypothesis of the South Pacific origin of the decadal (7-35 years) ENSO-like variation is investigated based on 200-year outputs of the ECHAM4/OPA/OASIS coupled GCM. Associated with the decadal warm (cold) SST anomalies in the tropical Pacific, an anomalous cyclonic (anticyclonic) circulation, which is tilted in a southeast-northwest direction, appears in the South Pacific. This results in anomalous upward (downward) Ekman pumping along the northeastern edge of the anomalous circulation and, hence, shallowing (deepening) the oceanic thermocline there. Such an external source of heat content tends to slowly discharge/recharge the tropical ocean on the decadal timescale. The above result is consistent with the observational study of Luo and Yamagata [2001]. Besides, the model reproduces amazingly a high lagged-correlation between the global land surface temperature and the decadal Nino3 SST. Despite the model biases, this suggests a potential prediction skill of the global warming based on the ENSO-like decadal variation. Copyright 2003 by the American Geophysical Union.",,"Correlation methods; Global warming; Storms; Temperature distribution; Tropics; Anticyclones; Surface temperatures; Climatology; atmosphere-ocean coupling; decadal variation; El Nino-Southern Oscillation; general circulation model",,,,,,"Bratcher, A.J., Giese, B.S., Tropical Pacific decadal variability and global warming (2002) Geophys. Res. Lett., 29 (19), p. 1918. , doi:10.1029/2002GLO15191; Giese, B.S., Urizar S.C. Fučkar, N., Southern hemisphere origins of the 1976 climate shift (2002) Geophys. Res. Lett., 29 (2). , doi:10.1029/2001GLO13268; Gu, D.F., Philander, S.H., Interdecal climate fluctuations that depend on exchanges between the tropics and extratropics (1997) Science, 275, pp. 805-807; Gualdi, S., Navarra, A., Guilyardi, E., Delecluse, P., Assessment of the tropical Indo-Pacific climate in the SINTEX CGCM (2003) Annals Geophysics, 46, pp. 1-26; Guilyardi, E., Delecluse, P., Gualdi, S., Navarra, A., Mechanisms for ENSO phase change in a coupled GCM (2003) J. Climate, 16, pp. 1141-1158; Jin, F.F., An equatorial ocean recharge paradigm for ENSO, part I: Conceptual model (1997) J. Atmos. Sci., 54, pp. 811-829; Kirtman, B.P., Schopf, P.S., Decadal variability in ENSO predictability and prediction (1998) J. Climate, 11, pp. 2804-2822; Kleeman, R., McCreary, J.P., Klinger, B.A., A mechanism for generating ENSO decadal variability (1999) Geophys. Res. Lett., 26, pp. 1743-1746; Knutson, T.R., Manabe, S., Model assessment of decadal variability and trends in the tropical Pacific Ocean (1998) J. Climate, 11, pp. 2273-2296; Lau, N.C., Interactions between global SST anomalies and the midlatitude atmospheric circulation (1997) Bull. Am. Meteorol. Soc., 78, pp. 21-33; Lau, N.C., Nath, M.J., A modeling study of the relative roles of tropical and extratropical SST anomalies in the variability of the global atmosphere-ocean system (1994) J. Climate, 7, pp. 1184-1207; Luo, J.-J., Yamagata, T., Long-tem El Niño-Southern Oscillation (ENSO)-like variation with special emphasis on the South Pacific (2001) J. Geophys. Res., 106, pp. 22211-22227; Madec, G., Delecluse, P., Imbard, M., Levy, C., OPA 8.1 ocean general circulation model reference manual (1998) LODYC/IPSL Technical Report, Note 11, p. 91. , Paris; Nitta, T., Yamada, S., Recent warming of tropical sea surface temperature and its relationship to the Northern Hemisphere circulation (1989) J. Meteorol. Soc. Japan, 67, pp. 375-383; Pan Y., H., Oort, A.H., Global climate variations connected with sea surface temperature anomalies in the eastern equatorial Pacific Ocean for the 1958-1973 period (1983) Mon. Wea. Rev., 111, pp. 1244-1258; Roeckner, E., (1996) The Atmospheric General Circulation Model ECHAM-4: Model Description and Simulation of Present-day Climate, p. 90. , Max-Planck-Institut für Meteorologie, Report No. 218, Hamburg; Timmermann, A., Jin, F.-F., A nonlinear mechanism for decadal El Niño amplitude changes (2002) Geophys. Res. Lett., 29 (1). , doi:10.1029/2001GLO13369; Torrence, C., Compo, G.P., A practical guide to wavelet analysis (1998) Bull. Am. Meteorol. Soc., 79, pp. 61-78; Yukimoto, S., Endoh, M., Kitamura, Y., Kitoh, A., Moloi, T., Noda, A., ENSO-like interclecadal variability in the Pacific Ocean as simulated in a coupled general circulation model (2000) J. Geophys. Res., 105, pp. 13945-13963; Valcke, S., Terray, L., Piacentini, A., (2000) The OASIS Coupler User Guide Version 2.4, p. 85. , Technical Report, CERFACE, Toulouse; Wang, B., Interdecadal changes in El Niño onset in the last four decades (1995) J. Climate, 8, pp. 267-285","Luo, J.-J.; Frontier Res. S